value.value: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the probasitarsus and calcar.
The rim that surrounds the antennal foramen.
The antennomere that is an appendage segment.
The area that is delimited by two transverse edges extending just ventrally and dorsally of the antennal foramina.
The sulcus that surrounds the antennal rim.
The anatomical structure that is delimited by the proximal and distal margins of the antennal sclerite.
The mandibular muscle that arises posterolaterally from the cranium and inserts on the tendon attached posteroproximal part of the mandible.
The area that is located distally on the lateral mesofurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral anterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle.
The area that is projected, located anteriorly on the preaxilla and fits into the dorsal incision of the pronotum.
The sclerite of the anterior glossal plate that is lateral to the median conjunctiva of the anterior glossal plate.
The labral muscle that is unpaired, arises proximally from the upper face and inserts on the median proximal margin of the labrum.
The ridge that delimits the site of origin of the anterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle.
The mesofurco-mesolaterophragmal muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts anteriorly on the mesolaterophragma.
The area that is limited posteriorly by the anterior mesopleural sulcus.
The sulcus that extends between the lateral end of the acetabular carina and the dorsal margin of the mesopleuron anterior to the mesopleural wing articulation.
The mesofurcal muscle that originates from the mesopleuron and inserts distally on the mesofurca.
The fossa that is located posterolaterally on the preaxilla and articulates with the anterior condyle of the first axillary sclerite of the fore wing.

label.value: anterior process of the mesofurcal bridge

value.value: The apodeme that is located medially on the mesofurcal bridge.
The process that is located medially on the anterior rim of pronotum.
The projection that is median and is located on the anterior margin of the basisternum.
The ridge that extends along the median line of the dorsal profurcal lamella and that receives the site of attachment of the profurco-laterocervical muscle.
The area that extends along the anterior margin of the pronotum and is delimited posteriorly by the transverse pronotal suclus.
The tentorial pit that corresponds to the anterior end of the tentorium and partially delimits the clypeus.
The notch that is located anteriorly on the dorsal margin of the mesopleuron and accommodates the mesobasalare.
The signum that is submedian and located on the anterior margin of the mesoscutum and corresponds to the site of origin of the longitudinal flight muscle.
The depression that is located anterolaterally on the abdominal tergum 2 and accommodates the propodeal tooth.
The corner that is located anterolaterally on the mesoscutum and is adjacent to the dorsal pronotal corner.
The ridge that extends parallel to the anterior (ventral) margin of the pronotum and delimits dorsally the site of origin of the pronoto-propleural arm muscles.
The inflection that is located on the anteroventral margin of the pronotum.
The area that is median, concave, triangular, is located on the posterior margin of the pronotum and is delimited by a carina anteriorly.
The apodeme that is located medially on the proximoventral margin of the gonostipes and is the site of origin of the ventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscles.
The area that extends distally of the apex of the velum or comb of the spur.
The depression accommodates the sensilla that is located ventrally on the  apical flagellomere.
The flagellomere that is located distally on the flagellum.
The seta that is located close to the distoventral margin of the gonostyle/volsella complex just laterally of the gonostyle/volsella complex-gonossiculus articulation.
The process that located distomedially on the labrum.
The row of spurs that is located on the internal margin of the calcar distally of the velum.
The area that is the distal part of the gonossiculus and is connected to the parossiculus via membranous conjunctiva.
The process that is internal.
The apodeme that is tubercle-like or spine-like.
The anatomical structure that is encircled by the evagination of the integument and whose integumental components are attached to the body via muscles.
The anatomical structure of the cuticle that is delimited by material or immaterial anatomical entities.
The wing cell of the fore wing that is minute, round and is delimited by the radio-medial cross veins.
The lobe that is connected proximodorsally with the manubrium and proximoventrally with the planta.
The anatomical line that extends on the border between two articulating sclerites.
The projection that bears the articular surface.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of two adjacent articular surfaces.
The impression that is on the first valvifer-first valvula complex accommodates the rhachis.
The sclerite that is located between the unguitractor and the bases of claws.
The area that is located posterior to the transscutal articulation and anterior to the scutoscutellar suture.
